                <note rend="inline" type="source">839.6463/110: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Russell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-04-16T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 16, 1923—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. Reference Welles’ 47, April 12, 11 a.m.</p>
                <p>Department would be very glad if Provisional Government and representatives
                    San[to] Domingo Water, Light and Power Company can make a mutually satisfactory
                    agreement <hi rend="italic">ad referendum</hi> for the purchase of the Company’s
                    properties by the municipalities of Santiago and Puerto Plata.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
